	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />DPCM means &quot;differential pulse code modulation&quot; because it stores the <em>difference</em> between one sample and the next. Sometimes it's referred to as &quot;delta pulse code modulation&quot; using a Greek letter Î” that often means difference between adjacent values in a sequence. In the NES scene, unqualified DPCM has a very specific meaning: the format accepted by the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC" class="postlink">APU's waveform playback unit</a> at $4010-$4013, a 1-bit little-endian DPCM with a 64-step range.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


